Key Match Events: David Wiese scored 13 runs off 4 balls in the Super Over
Wiese bowled brilliantly, limiting Oman to only 10 runs in the Super Over
Post-Match Reflections: David Wiese stated that he 'aged a couple of years' older and that the evening had been emotionally draining
Wiese also stated that the pitch was two-paced, requiring a batter to take some time before going crazy over bowlers
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the first Super Over in a men's T20 World Cup tournament since 2012
Others: The match at Kensington Oval went to a super over following a nail-biting low-scoring duel in which Oman was swept out for 109 runs
Namibia's run chase then stuttered as Oman's Mehran Khan's outstanding bowling effort saw them finish on 109-6, setting up the Super Over drama
